sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as ML Model / Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant FS as Feature Server<br/>6566/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant SecMgr as SecurityManager<br/>(in-process)
    participant Redis as Online Store (Redis)<br/>6379/TCP
    participant BQ as Offline Store (BigQuery)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Registry as Registry<br/>6001/TCP gRPC
    participant Operator as Feast Operator
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant CronJob as Materialization CronJob

    Note over Client,Redis: Flow 1: Online Feature Retrieval
    Client->>Route: POST /get-online-features<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OIDC/K8s)
    Route->>FS: Forward (TLS edge termination)
    FS->>SecMgr: Validate token & check<br/>Permission: READ_ONLINE
    SecMgr-->>FS: Authorized
    FS->>Redis: GET feature values<br/>Auth: Password, TLS optional
    Redis-->>FS: Feature values
    FS-->>Route: JSON Response
    Route-->>Client: Feature values

    Note over CronJob,Redis: Flow 2: Feature Materialization (CronJob)
    CronJob->>FS: kubectl exec<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount RBAC
    FS->>BQ: Query historical features<br/>Auth: GCP credentials, TLS 1.2+
    BQ-->>FS: Feature data (batch)
    FS->>Redis: Write materialized features<br/>Auth: Password, TLS optional
    Redis-->>FS: ACK

    Note over Client,Redis: Flow 3: Feature Push
    Client->>Route: POST /push<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Route->>FS: Forward
    FS->>SecMgr: Check Permission:<br/>WRITE_ONLINE / WRITE_OFFLINE
    SecMgr-->>FS: Authorized
    FS->>Redis: Write to online store<br/>(immediate)
    FS->>BQ: Write to offline store<br/>(batched, background)

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Operator Auto-Access RBAC
    Operator->>FS: GET /api/v1/permissions<br/>Port: 8001/TCP<br/>Auth: Intra-communication JWT
    FS-->>Operator: Permission policies
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update RBAC resources<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: RBAC resources created
